values:
I think I&nbsp;have finally gotten to a point in my life where those in my life, may not be the closest people to me, may not be the people I know the best, (yet), may not be the people I&nbsp;get to see all the time.&nbsp; They are the ones who are there when I&nbsp;need a shoulder, an ear and a helping hand.

Because of you, the true ones, I am able to go to events like SoCal Decom and Elysium, I will be able to get testing supplies for my diabetes control, support through this search for a home (which I&nbsp;am able to achieve only because I have generous in-laws).&nbsp; 

The users, the abusers and those who generally were no good in my life seem to have left, been pushed away or otherwise purged.&nbsp;&nbsp;I feel healthy in a social manner.&nbsp; Much more so than I&nbsp;have been in a long time.&nbsp; 

My desire to have friends led me to allow people into my life who had no place.&nbsp;&nbsp;People who took, took and took and gave nothing in return.&nbsp; 

You've stood by me as I&nbsp;ranted and raved. &nbsp;You stood by me in support letting me know it wasn't just me.&nbsp; You stood by me when it was just me...lol

Thank you all. &nbsp;I love you!
